21 SECTION 4. DO NOT CODIFY. The Supreme Court has interpreted domicile to
22 require "actual residence plus the intent to remain in a particular place".
23 Leathers v. Womack, 341 Ark. 609, 618 (2000). An individual may have only one
24 (1) domicile, and circumstances must present "a bona fide intention of making
25 it a fixed and permanent place of abode". Id. at. 619.
